<!-- post # 8 --><font color="#FF0000">THOUGHTS</font><br><tt>Mon Nov 11 16:00:28 US/Eastern 1996</tt><p>I am reading this page on Veterans Day, 1996.  Don't ask me about the coincidence - Vietnam has been on my mind all day.<br><br>Others who have responded here have wanted to once again politicize the conflict... I just want to remember my friends.  I lost so much in that war - and gained so much - that I will never be able to tell of the true impact.  I really don't want to tell about it.  If you were there in a line unit you understand what I mean.<br><br>What I do know is, that as terrible as it was, I would give anything to be able to go back.  There is nothing more pure or more perfect than the love, trust and protection of the common American soldier in combat.  I will miss this for the rest of my life.<p><code>-- wharton@scra.org  (C.A. Wharton) </code><p>